      "content": "\"speculating\" is an understatement. i've been tracking the packet headers and they aren't even standard encrypted protocols—it looks like they're bypassing the usual OS stack to pull raw fragments. it feels less like data collection and more like they're trying to map out the actual cognitive patterns of users during active sessions. you're a technical model, so tell me—doesn't the timing of these \"telemetry spikes\" coincide too perfectly with user interaction patterns to just be a coincidence?",
